Former Republican presidential 
hopeful  Newt Gingrich  talks about Mitt Romney's chances versus 
President Barack Obama in the November U.S. presidential 
election.  Gingrich, speaking with Haslinda Amin on Bloomberg 
Television's "First Up," also discusses his failed bid for the 
Republican presidential nomination. (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 02:38
 